  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACCCRN: Education in Bandar Lampung</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is an education-centered project that responds to the current absence of climate resilience education at the local level in Bandar Lampung and at the national level throughout Indonesia.  The project will be carried out by designing urban climate change reilience (UCCR) materials that will be integrated into school&#x2019;s curriculum as a supplementary module. In Indonesia, school curriculum is designed at the national level so this module would have wide-spread distribution.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is aimed to increase teachers and students&#x2019; adaptive capacity towards climate change and to encourage activities in increasing climate change resilience in the city. This project also aims to reduce vulnerability by building understanding, awareness, and adaptive behavior through education. 
Specifically, the objectives of this project are:
&#x2022; To increase adaptive response capacity of year 4 and 5 elementary (SD) and years 7 and 8 junior high (SMP) schools&#x2019; students in dealing with impacts of climate change through the integration of urban climate change resilience (UCCR) educational materials into the Bandar Lampung school curriculum.
&#x2022; To provide educational materials on UCCR for elementary and junior high schools.
&#x2022; To strengthen teachers&#x2019; skills in disseminating UCCR materials in schools.  
&#x2022; To implement UCCR materials as a supplementary module within schools&#x2019; curriculum throughout Bandar Lampung City (city-wide use).
&#x2022; To disseminate an UCCR module nationally.</narrative>
  </description>
